Date: Fri, 18 Nov 2016 16:01:08 -0400 (AST)=0A=
From: selinger@mathstat.dal.ca (Peter Selinger)=0A=
=0A=
I would like to add that the correct plural of "color" is "colores".=0A=
Because as everybody knows, "color" is a Latin noun. For example, here=0A=
is a citation: "Omnes vero se Britanni vitro inficiunt, quod caeruleum=0A=
efficit colorem, atque hoc horridiores sunt in pugna aspectu" (Caesar,=0A=
Commentarii de bello Gallico, Liber V.14.2)". Proving that "color" is=0A=
a noun. Therefore, I urge everyone to use "colores" instead of the=0A=
incorrect "colors" (or worse, "colours")! -- Peter=0A=
=0A=
