From: Tadeusz Litak <tadeusz.litak@gmail.com>=0A=
Date: Sat, 19 Nov 2016 03:25:16 +0100=0A=
On 18/11/16 17:33, Johannes Huebschmann wrote:=0A=
> The correct plural form of "topos" is "topoi",=0A=
> as the plural form of "logos" is "logoi". =0A=
=0A=
Yes, this what ancient Greek would dictate.=0A=
=0A=
However, people have argued convincingly that "toposes" is in fact the form=
  intended by Grothendieck.=0A=
=0A=
See, for example, footnote 4 in McLarty's =E2=80=9CThe Uses and Abuses of t=
he History of Topos Theory=E2=80=9D.=0A=
=0A=
Moreover, the plural form "topoi" is used for too many notions in the human=
ities (including journal titles). Just try =0A=
googling for it. And then google for "toposes", for comparison.=0A=
=0A=
To me, "topoi" is the plural form for the notion from rhetoric and "Literat=
urwissenschaft":=0A=
=0A=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literary_topos=0A=
=0A=
https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topos_(Geisteswissenschaft)=0A=
=0A=


